  Batha  .","German: from an ancient Germanic personal name formed with the element <i>badu</i> ‘battle’."],"variants":[{"name":"Bath","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dalbir, Renu, Sandeep, Suneet, Tarlok, Vikram.","English (southern): habitational name from the city of Bath in Somerset, or possibly from Bathe Barton in North Tawton in Devon, or some other minor places so called. The city of Bath is the site of the sumptuous, but in the Middle Ages ruined, Roman baths. The place is named with the dative plural of Old English <i>bæth</i> ‘bath’. In some cases the surname may have originated as a metonymic occupational name for an attendant at a public bath house.","German: variant of   Bathe  ."]}]},{"name":"Bartholomew","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of New Testament origin, the name of an apostle mentioned in all the synoptic gospels (Matthew, Mark, and Luke) and in the Acts of the Apostles. It is an Aramaic formation meaning ‘son of Talmai’, and has been assumed by many scholars to be a byname of the apostle   Nathaniel .  <i>Talmai</i> is a Hebrew name, said to mean ‘abounding in furrows’ (Numbers 13:22)."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Bartholomew Bathe II was born in 1419, in Diocese of Meath, Ireland as the son of Barron Richard Luttrell and Margrette Fitz- Leon. He married Catherine Uriel in 1443, in Diocese of Meath, Ireland. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1477, in his hometown, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1419–1477":"1419–1477","1428–Female":"1428–Surnud","1445–Male":"1445–Surnud","1460–1540":"1460–1540","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1445":"1445","1477":"1477","1443":"1443","1540":"1540","1460":"1460","1419":"1419","about 1460":"umbes 1460","1428":"1428","Dullardstown, Meath, Leinster, Ireland":"Diocese of Meath, Iirimaa","Diocese of Meath, Leinster, Ireland":"Diocese of Meath, Iirimaa","County Meath, Irel